New South Capital Management Inc. Sells 8,841 Shares of Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. (NYSE:SWK)


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments




New South Capital Management Inc. decreased its stake in shares of  Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. (NYSE:SWK) by 1.7% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The firm owned 515,014 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 8,841 shares during the period. Stanley Black & Decker comprises  1.6% of New South Capital Management Inc.’s portfolio, making the stock its 27th largest position. New South Capital Management Inc. owned 0.34% of Stanley Black & Decker worth $68,430,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Several other institutional investors have also recently bought and sold shares of SWK. Pensionfund Sabic purchased a new position in  Stanley Black & Decker during the first quarter valued at $1,701,000.  Macquarie Group Ltd. raised its position in  Stanley Black & Decker by 55.3% in the fourth quarter. Macquarie Group Ltd. now owns 170,688 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $19,576,000 after buying an additional 60,745 shares during the period.  Highbridge Capital Management LLC purchased a new position in  Stanley Black & Decker during the fourth quarter valued at $8,843,000.  Kentucky Retirement Systems Insurance Trust Fund purchased a new position in  Stanley Black & Decker during the fourth quarter valued at $560,000.  Finally, Kentucky Retirement Systems purchased a new position in  Stanley Black & Decker during the fourth quarter valued at $1,254,000. 83.60% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Stanley Black & Decker Inc. alerts:



Shares of Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. (NYSE SWK) opened at 146.79 on Friday. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $142.29 and its 200-day moving average is $132.66. Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. has a 52 week low of $111.89 and a 52 week high of $148.32. The stock has a market capitalization of $22.45 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 18.74 and a beta of 1.10. 





Stanley Black & Decker (NYSE:SWK) last issued its earnings results on Friday, April 21st. The industrial products company reported $1.29 EPS for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $1.19 by $0.10. Stanley Black & Decker had a return on equity of 15.47% and a net margin of 10.13%. The firm had revenue of $2.81 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $2.76 billion. During the same quarter in the previous year, the company posted $1.28 earnings per share. The business’s quarterly revenue was up 5.0% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, equities research analysts anticipate that  Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. will post $7.23 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Tuesday, September 19th. Shareholders of record on Friday, September 1st will be paid a $0.63 dividend. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, August 30th. This represents a $2.52 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 1.72%. This is an increase from Stanley Black & Decker’s previous quarterly dividend of $0.58. Stanley Black & Decker’s payout ratio is 29.67%. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: This report was originally  published by Chaffey Breeze and is the sole property of of Chaffey Breeze. If you are reading this report on another website, it was illegally stolen and reposted in violation of U.S. & international trademark and copyright legislation. The legal version of this report can be read at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/23/stanley-black-decker-inc-nyseswk-shares-sold-by-new-south-capital-management-inc-updated-updated.html. 
A number of equities research analysts recently issued reports on the stock. FBR & Co  reissued an “outperform” rating on shares of Stanley Black & Decker in a research note on Tuesday, July 11th. Zacks Investment Research cut shares of Stanley Black & Decker from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research note on Thursday, July 13th. Wolfe Research assumed coverage on shares of Stanley Black & Decker in a research note on Tuesday, July 11th. They issued an “outperform” rating and a $160.00 price target on the stock. MKM Partners assumed coverage on shares of Stanley Black & Decker in a research note on Friday, July 7th. They issued a “buy” rating and a $166.00 price target on the stock. Finally, BidaskClub raised shares of Stanley Black & Decker from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating in a research note on Friday, June 16th. Five research analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and twelve have assigned  a buy rating to the company’s stock. The company currently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and an average target price of $152.58.
In other Stanley Black & Decker news, SVP Jaime A. Ramirez sold 10,440 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction dated Friday, June 9th. The stock was sold at an average price of $139.56, for a total value of $1,457,006.40. Following the transaction, the senior vice president now owns 41,541 shares in the company, valued at $5,797,461.96. The sale was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is accessible through the SEC website. Insiders own  1.15% of the company’s stock. 
Stanley Black & Decker Company Profile
Stanley Black & Decker, Inc is a global provider of hand tools, power tools and related accessories, mechanical access solutions, such as automatic doors and commercial locking systems, electronic security and monitoring systems, healthcare solutions, engineered fastening systems, and products and services for various industrial applications.







