Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. (NYSE:SWK) Stake Lowered by BerganKDV Wealth Management LLC

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 27th, 2017 // No Comments 

BerganKDV Wealth Management LLC reduced its stake in shares of Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. (NYSE:SWK) by 4.7% during the second quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The fund owned 6,442 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 319 shares during the period. BerganKDV Wealth Management LLC’s holdings in Stanley Black & Decker were worth $907,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Several other hedge funds have also recently made changes to their positions in the stock. Thompson Davis & CO. Inc. bought a new position in shares of Stanley Black & Decker during the first quarter worth about $108,000. Alexandria Capital LLC increased its position in shares of Stanley Black & Decker by 3.3% in the first quarter. Alexandria Capital LLC now owns 826 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $110,000 after buying an additional 26 shares during the period. Independent Portfolio Consultants Inc. increased its position in shares of Stanley Black & Decker by 87.8% in the second quarter. Independent Portfolio Consultants Inc. now owns 986 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $139,000 after buying an additional 461 shares during the period. Tompkins Financial Corp increased its position in shares of Stanley Black & Decker by 689.6% in the first quarter. Tompkins Financial Corp now owns 987 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $104,000 after buying an additional 862 shares during the period. Finally, Coconut Grove Bank increased its position in shares of Stanley Black & Decker by 98.4% in the first quarter. Coconut Grove Bank now owns 1,010 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $134,000 after buying an additional 501 shares during the period. 83.83% of the stock is currently owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Stanley Black & Decker Inc. alerts:



Shares of Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. (NYSE:SWK) traded up 0.61% during trading on Thursday, reaching $141.14. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 1,071,179 shares. Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. has a 12-month low of $111.89 and a 12-month high of $148.32. The company has a 50 day moving average of $142.85 and a 200 day moving average of $133.41. The company has a market cap of $21.59 billion, a PE ratio of 18.02 and a beta of 1.10. 




Stanley Black & Decker (NYSE:SWK) last released its quarterly earnings data on Monday, July 24th. The industrial products company reported $2.01 EPS for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $1.96 by $0.05. The company had revenue of $3.23 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $3.18 billion. Stanley Black & Decker had a net margin of 9.92% and a return on equity of 14.93%. Stanley Black & Decker’s quarterly revenue was up 10.1% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter in the prior year, the firm earned $1.84 EPS. On average, analysts anticipate that Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. will post $7.29 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Tuesday, September 19th. Stockholders of record on Friday, September 1st will be issued a dividend of $0.63 per share. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Wednesday, August 30th. This represents a $2.52 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 1.79%. This is an increase from Stanley Black & Decker’s previous quarterly dividend of $0.58. Stanley Black & Decker’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is currently 29.74%. 
